JOHANNESBURG – Airports Company South Africa (Acsa) has expressed concern at reports that a donation amounting to R5-million of its donation to the Black Business Council has disappeared. The airport's management company says the amount was paid in two installments earlier this year into the account of a company called Merit Energy. Merit Energy had been appointed to drive a campaign for economic transformation. READ: ACSA announces reduction in tariffs Acsa says these payments were made in accordance with its systems and were duly recorded. The Black Business Council has asked audit firm Sizwe Ntsaluba Gobodo to investigate why the funds never made it into its bank account. eNCA